				<small>February 7th, 2007 <!-- by jeremy --></small>

				<div class="entry">
					<p>You can read the full text of the bill, and get a summary of the progress of the bill, through the <a href="http://leg1.state.va.us/cgi-bin/legp504.exe?071+sum+HJ728">Virginia General Assembly Legislative Information System.</a> A few interesting newspaper articles and editorials about the bill include <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/01/16/AR2007011600995.html?nav=rss_email/components">Fury Over Delagate&#8217;s Remarks on Slavery&#8221;</a> (<em>Washington Post</em>),  <a href="http://content.hamptonroads.com/story.cfm?story=118602&#038;ran=159118">&#8220;Wording of Resolution Changed on Va&#8217;s Slavery Role&#8221; (<em>Virginian-Pilot</em>)</a>, a <a href="mms://wmvod.mgnetwork.com/vod/rtd/20070129_caplive.wmv">Monday, Jan. 29 webcast by the Richmond Times-Dispatch highlighting the state Senate&#8217;s debate over language</a>, <a href="http://www.roanoke.com/editorials/taylor/wb/101409">&#8220;Pain and Apology&#8221;</a> and <a href="http://www.roanoke.com/editorials/strother/wb/101410">All Due Apologies&#8221;</a> (editorials in the <em>Roanoke Times</em>). I haven&#8217;t been able to find editorials in newspapers criticizing the apology, so if you find some please post links to them in the comments.</p>
				</div>

